00:36:56,705 --> 00:36:59,674
was our first American gig,
in Washington.

516
00:36:59,742 --> 00:37:03,542
And they stuck us there
and kept asking Ringo to move his kit.

517
00:37:03,646 --> 00:37:07,912
He had to physically move them each
time. I remember, poor Ringo was facing...

518
00:37:07,983 --> 00:37:12,716
We'd never seen the likes of it. They're
saying, "But you've got to do this."

519
00:37:12,788 --> 00:37:15,951
We said, "No!"
They said, "Yeah, there's audience there."

520
00:37:16,025 --> 00:37:19,756
We said, "Well, they'll just see our backs."
"No, you've got to move."

521
00:37:19,828 --> 00:37:23,992
So we're moving. Poor old Ringo
picking up his bloody drum kit

522
00:37:24,066 --> 00:37:26,728
and repositioning it
between numbers.

523
00:37:26,835 --> 00:37:30,737
- And then, to make it worse, jelly babies!
- (George Martin) Yeah.

524
00:37:30,839 --> 00:37:33,569
- (McCartney) The stage...
- They were thrown at you.

525
00:37:33,676 --> 00:37:36,543
We'd said that our favorite sweet
was jelly babies,

526
00:37:36,645 --> 00:37:40,479
so all the Americans threw them at us -
Bassett's jelly babies.

527
00:37:40,549 --> 00:37:44,383
And the whole bloody floor
was like glue.

528
00:37:45,387 --> 00:37:48,982
("I Want to Hold Your Hand")

529
00:37:52,161 --> 00:37:54,493
Oh, yeah, I'll

530
00:37:54,597 --> 00:37:56,758
Tell you something

531
00:37:56,832 --> 00:37:59,801
(Starr) I just loved
the front line of that band.

532
00:37:59,868 --> 00:38:02,359
You know,
John, Paul and George were that band.

533
00:38:02,471 --> 00:38:07,067
And in Liverpool, if they were playing,
it'd be, like, a band I would go and see

534
00:38:07,142 --> 00:38:09,940
if I wasn't playing
in the band I was with.

535
00:38:10,012 --> 00:38:14,745
And then, by chance, there was a knock
on the door at 12 o'clock in the afternoon

536
00:38:14,817 --> 00:38:20,119
and Brian Epstein said, "Would you
play with the Beatles just for today?"

537
00:38:20,189 --> 00:38:23,784
And I did,
and that's how we became friends.

538
00:38:26,862 --> 00:38:30,389
We were just a couple of kids
walking around town in black

539
00:38:30,466 --> 00:38:34,027
with a guitar over our backs,
walking down the streets like that.

540
00:38:34,103 --> 00:38:36,435
So I remember that -
the very beginnings -

541
00:38:36,505 --> 00:38:41,738
or just going to John's house
and learning chords and playing things.

542
00:38:41,844 --> 00:38:46,372
Then it would be, like, in hotel rooms,
and saying, "OK, I've got a bit of an idea."

543
00:38:46,482 --> 00:38:48,541
So you'd fire off each other.

544
00:38:48,617 --> 00:38:52,314
And it nearly always took us
about three hours, top.

545
00:38:52,388 --> 00:38:55,414
We never took
any longer than three hours.

546
00:38:55,524 --> 00:38:58,049
And every day we did it,

547
00:38:58,160 --> 00:39:01,027
every single time
we came to do it,

548
00:39:01,096 --> 00:39:03,394
we did it.
We finished a song.

549
00:39:03,465 --> 00:39:08,732
We had a knack for it.
We understood what we were trying to do.

