01:01:47,628 --> 01:01:50,096
- (man) If only you could feel them.
- Exactly.

869
01:01:50,197 --> 01:01:54,258
Do you think this is a departure,
this is a change for Cirque?

870
01:01:54,335 --> 01:01:56,860
The dancing, the staging,
the way it's presented?

871
01:01:56,937 --> 01:02:00,964
Yeah, it is. This is more a musical
than a Cirque show.

872
01:02:01,509 --> 01:02:04,569
- You could have told us!
- Huh?

873
01:02:04,678 --> 01:02:09,775
Yeah, you know, 'cause I think
people are gonna be surprised.

874
01:02:09,850 --> 01:02:14,344
- In terms of not having many acrobatics?
- I hope they're not disappointed.

875
01:02:14,422 --> 01:02:16,322
- Yeah, that type...
- Well...

876
01:02:16,390 --> 01:02:19,359
I don't think they expect...
People will come for the music,

877
01:02:19,427 --> 01:02:22,760
the encounter of the Cirque du Soleil
and the Beatles.

878
01:02:22,830 --> 01:02:26,823
Now it's a question of tidying up things
and clarifying things.

879
01:02:26,901 --> 01:02:31,429
That's why it's important to get... That's
what I like about the opinion of Yoko.

880
01:02:31,505 --> 01:02:34,440
This is what we need,
because we were not there with them.

881
01:02:34,508 --> 01:02:37,671
You know, especially with Yoko and you,
we were not there.

882
01:02:37,745 --> 01:02:42,808
With George I didn't have time
to go into detail of each of the songs.

883
01:02:42,917 --> 01:02:45,351
I want to make sure
the details are addressed.

884
01:02:45,419 --> 01:02:48,320
Like I said, at the end
we have to make a decision

885
01:02:48,389 --> 01:02:53,850
because we can't do a show
in a community way.

886
01:02:53,961 --> 01:02:57,920
As long as there is something...
each one has something going,

887
01:02:58,032 --> 01:03:01,001
- and there's some focus.
- But it's the same thing.

888
01:03:01,068 --> 01:03:04,162
That's what I always bring back
to the people I work with.

889
01:03:04,271 --> 01:03:08,503
I said, "It's not about
who has the best idea."

890
01:03:08,576 --> 01:03:11,204
"It's what is the best idea,
who will prevail."

891
01:03:11,312 --> 01:03:15,976
Of course, everybody has
his personality, his pride

892
01:03:16,050 --> 01:03:19,247
and his ego,
and I totally understand that.

893
01:03:19,353 --> 01:03:22,186
But at the end, we're all there
to serve one thing -

894
01:03:22,256 --> 01:03:24,247
- the show for the public.
- The show.

895
01:03:24,358 --> 01:03:29,057
They will decide who will live or die
with what we do.

896
01:03:53,921 --> 01:03:57,948
(Proteau) In Montreal, I have a family.
I have three sons.

897
01:03:58,025 --> 01:04:00,289
May we present the Beatles?

898
01:04:00,394 --> 01:04:04,125
So this is a kind of sacrifice
that maybe I do.

899
01:04:05,199 --> 01:04:10,694
The last time I saw them was at the end
of March because my father died.

900
01:04:14,942 --> 01:04:22,144
When I open the show, I just feel that...
that I'm doing that for my father.

901
01:04:33,194 --> 01:04:37,528
I bring a message from Apple,
my boss Neil Aspinall,

902
01:04:37,631 --> 01:04:41,123
and from Paul and Ringo
and Yoko and Olivia

903
01:04:41,235 --> 01:04:43,328
to wish you the very best for tonight,

904
01:04:43,437 --> 01:04:49,774
and express their profound respect for
your skill, your energy, your courage.

905
01:04:49,877 --> 01:04:52,607
One day, this will all seem
like a long time ago,

906
01:04:52,713 --> 01:04:57,116
so savor the moment,
and you have my best wishes.

907
01:05:05,492 --> 01:05:09,758
(Champagne) We all know we worked
really hard. It was not an easy one.

908
01:05:09,830 --> 01:05:15,427
All the Beatles themselves - Paul, Ringo,
Yoko and Olivia and their family,

909
01:05:15,502 --> 01:05:21,668
tonight we have the honor to have also
Cynthia Lennon, first wife of John Lennon,

910
01:05:21,742 --> 01:05:27,738
is going to be here with Julian Lennon
and Sean, and Dhani Harrison.

911
01:05:27,815 --> 01:05:31,546
And all those people gathered around
with what you've done,

912
01:05:31,619 --> 01:05:35,111
with what we've all done together.

913
01:05:35,189 --> 01:05:37,350
I think it's great that...

914
01:05:37,424 --> 01:05:39,449
You know, bodies go.

915
01:05:39,560 --> 01:05:45,430
George Harrison is dead, but we can
really say that his spirit is with us.

916
01:05:47,001 --> 01:05:51,529
And we gave a body
to that spirit all together.

917
01:05:51,639 --> 01:05:53,834
- Peace and love. I love you.
- (applause)

